  "texts": [
    "Four ORSA chips were used simultaneously to measure the target gas four times in succession at the same concentration, resulting in a total of 16-cycle gas sensing signals (Supplementary Fig. 10).",
    "One cycle of the signal consists of a total of 1410 discrete data points.",
    "In general, the time series characteristics of gas reaction data can be divided into (i) the section where the reaction begins and converges to the peak (gas reaction section), (ii) the section where air is injected as recovery gas, the gas molecules bound to the sensing material are removed, and the sensor begins to recover to its original state from the peak (recovery section), (iii) the section where the downward trend is stable due to long-term recovery (complete recovery section).",
    "Therefore, considering the time series characteristics of the gas detection signal, the signal of all 1410 points is divided into 3 sections at intervals of 470 points and feature processing is performed for each section.",
    "The sampling rate was set to 2820, which is twice the total data points."
  ],
